726409f-c.text:
Corona Avenue, east side, at 56th Avenue, viewing southward, showing dwellings on both corners of the street which have been converted into tourist accomodations for visitors to the New York World's Fair of 1939-40. View 3 shows the
S.E. corner of the two thoroughfares.
June 23, 1940
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
